Session Management Philosophy

Sessions are NEVER hard deleted.

Instead:

is_active = False

This preserves:

Security audit history
Suspicious activity tracking
Login analytics
Session debugging capability
Session Expiration Logic

The platform supports automatic inactive session cleanup.

Current timeout:

60 minutes

If a session remains inactive for too long:

is_active = False

This prevents:

Zombie sessions
Long-running abandoned sessions
False active session detection
Active Session Logic (Major Update)
Old Behavior

Previously:

If another device had an active session:

Login was blocked completely

This caused problems for legitimate users.

Example:

User logged in on phone
User later wanted to login on laptop
Phone session still existed
Laptop login blocked
New Session Behavior

The system now allows:

2 registered devices simultaneously

Users can:

Stay logged in on phone
Stay logged in on laptop

At the same time.

Anti-Account-Sharing Protection

Even though multiple devices can remain logged in:

The platform still prevents:

Simultaneous protected video playback

This means:

Browsing from two devices = Allowed
Watching protected videos simultaneously = Blocked

This provides:

Better user experience
Stronger anti-sharing protection
Less frustration for legitimate students
