Video Lock System

When a student starts a lesson video:

Backend checks:

Is another device already playing a video?

If YES:

Video playback is blocked

Error returned:

A video is already playing on another device.
Token Storage Security (Major Security Upgrade)
Previous Behavior

Previously:

Tokens were stored inside:

localStorage

Stored tokens:

access_token
refresh_token

This exposed the system to risks such as:

XSS token theft
JavaScript token access
Browser extension leakage
Token extraction attacks
New Secure Token Architecture

The platform now uses:

HttpOnly Cookie + Memory Token Architecture
Refresh Token Storage

Refresh Token is now stored inside:

HttpOnly Secure Cookie

Characteristics:

JavaScript CANNOT access it
Automatically sent with requests
Hidden from frontend code

This significantly improves security.

Access Token Storage

Access Token is now stored:

In memory only

inside frontend runtime.

Meaning:

NOT stored in localStorage
NOT stored in sessionStorage
NOT persisted permanently
Current localStorage Content

The frontend now stores ONLY:

device_id
device_name
user
role
username

No authentication tokens remain in localStorage.

Axios Security Architecture

Frontend Axios configuration now:

Automatically attaches Authorization headers
Automatically sends cookies
Automatically refreshes expired access tokens
Automatically redirects unauthorized users

Configuration:

withCredentials: true

This allows secure cookie communication between:

React Frontend
Django Backend
Automatic Access Token Refresh

When access token expires:

Axios interceptor automatically calls:

POST /api/security/refresh/

Backend:

Reads refresh token from HttpOnly Cookie
Generates new access token
Returns fresh access token securely

Frontend:

Updates memory token automatically
Retries original request

User experience remains seamless.

Logout Security

During logout:

Backend:

Blacklists refresh token
Deactivates current session
Deletes refresh token cookie

Frontend:

Clears user information
Clears memory token

Important:

device_id is NOT removed

This preserves stable device identity.

