Login Flow (Updated)
Step 1

User enters:

email / username / phone
password
Step 2

Frontend sends:

device_id
device_name

inside headers.

Step 3

Backend:

Validates credentials
Validates device
Checks device limit
Reactivates existing device if needed
Creates session
Generates JWT tokens
Step 4

Backend returns:

Access Token
User Information

And stores:

Refresh Token inside HttpOnly Cookie
Step 5

Frontend:

Stores access token in memory
Stores only user metadata in localStorage
